<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="269" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,1225,1754]" pageId="14" pageNumber="269">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1225,1250]" pageId="14" pageNumber="269">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Distinguished among species of 
<taxonomicName authority="Odontorhagus" authorityName="Odontorhagus" box="[657,979,1225,1250]" class="Insecta" family="Schizopteridae" genus="Schizoptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="269" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[657,790,1225,1249]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="269">Schizoptera</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[809,970,1225,1249]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="269">Odontorhagus</emphasis>
)
</taxonomicName>
by the ovoid body shape, the lack of a fuscous patch, and the cylindrical and tapering lateral process of the subgenital plate.
</paragraph>
