<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,1225,1754]" pageId="14" pageNumber="269">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,382,1369,1394]" pageId="14" pageNumber="269">Re-description.</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[388,446,1369,1393]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="269">Male</emphasis>
: length: 
<quantity box="[546,635,1369,1394]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="14" pageNumber="269" unit="mm" value="1.5">1.5 mm</quantity>
; body ovoid. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[788,990,1369,1394]" pageId="14" pageNumber="269">COLORATION:</emphasis>
general coloration dark brown; fuscous patch absent; Sc+C distinctly lighter than remainder of hemelytra (
<figureCitation box="[906,977,1405,1430]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1903,1925]" captionTargetBox="[151,1429,229,1867]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,229,1882]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 2. Habitus images of S. (Odontorhagus) species." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/164751/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="269">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[997,1375,1405,1430]" pageId="14" pageNumber="269">SURFACE AND VESTITURE:</emphasis>
as in subgeneric description. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[423,605,1441,1466]" pageId="14" pageNumber="269">STRUCTURE:</emphasis>
<collectionCode box="[614,696,1442,1466]" pageId="14" pageNumber="269">HEAD</collectionCode>
: flat dorsal view (
<figureCitation box="[907,978,1441,1466]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1903,1925]" captionTargetBox="[151,1429,229,1867]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,229,1882]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 2. Habitus images of S. (Odontorhagus) species." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/164751/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="269">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
); eyes about 1/2 as wide as synthlipsis. THORAX: as in subgeneric description; hemelytron as in subgeneric description; M2 vein straight, anterior membranal cell triangular. ABDOMEN: as in subgeneric description; stVI with small, tooth-like process on posterior margin; subgenital plate weakly asymmetrical; process of subgenital cylindrical and tapering.
</paragraph>
