<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="269" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,1225,1754]" pageId="14" pageNumber="269">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,332,1657,1682]" pageId="14" pageNumber="269">Discussion.</emphasis>
No additional specimens examined matched the description of this species, and ventral images of the 
<typeStatus box="[193,291,1693,1718]" pageId="14" pageNumber="269">holotype</typeStatus>
are unavailable because of the way the specimen was mounted; therefore our re-description is solely somatic. For an illustration of the subgenital plate of this species see 
<bibRefCitation author="McAtee" box="[923,1243,1729,1754]" pageId="14" pageNumber="269" refString="McAtee, W. L., &amp; Malloch, J. R. (1925) Revision of bugs of the family Cryptostemmatidae in the collection of the United States National Museum. Proceedings of the United States National Museum, 67 (13), 1 - 42." type="journal article" year="1925">McAtee and Malloch (1925)</bibRefCitation>
Figure 65.
</paragraph>
